        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 26 at 11:50PM MDT until July 27 at 12:15AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 1148 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 13 miles southeast of Bredette to 10 miles west of
Savage to 10 miles south of Glendive, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated. At 1135 pm, 60 mph wind was reported in
Poplar.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Sidney, Glendive, Wolf Point, Poplar, Culbertson, Circle, Wibaux,
Fallon, Fairview, Brockton, Bainville, Froid, Richey, Savage, West
Glendive, Intake, Bloomfield, Lambert, Vida, and Carlyle.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
